{"questionId":"33094614","questionHtml":"<p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></msqrt></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the greatest value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> exists, justifying your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>since we require&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> must be one to one)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>OR</p>\n<p>Does not obey horizontal line test for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33094614","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The function f is defined by fx=2x2-15x+18, where x∈ℝ, x≤k. Find the greatest value of k for which f-1 exists, justifying your answer.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse, inverse and domain restriction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}